column2: Partly cloudy- water okay- too cold for swimming.  The rain gauge reading from 5/20-6/8 is 0.5 inches.
Cloudy day and no lake algae.  We have had at least 4 inches of rain in last four weeks.
Cool- sunny- much algae for this lake- and lake is calm.  The rain gauge reading from 7/21-8/14 is 1.4 inches.
Too cold for swimming.  The rain gauge reading from 8/14-9/28 is 5.2 inches. with the north wind it was hard to hold the pontoon boat.
Water level up account high rainfall this year.
1993 a high water year.  Water still 6 inches over outlet baffle.
Cloudy day with some wind.  The temperature is 65 degrees.
Clear- 72 degrees at 7: 00 am- and calm.
It was windy yesterday.  Calm today but the lake is still stirred up.
The water is greenish brown.  The algae is all the way down.
Clear- sunny- 2 days of rain prior to sample.
Clear- sunny- 2 days heavy wind prior to sample.
Ice out april 1.  On/off rain last 2 weeks.
Lake level lower than august. 4/24-5/1 dry. 5/3-5/8 rain.
Partly sunny. rain in morning. 15-20 mph wind.
Heavy rains last night. partly sunny.
Ice out April 16 - Heavy rains last week.
Unusual weed build up. Partly sunny.
Little rain last two weeks. Cloudy.
Partly cloudy - 4 days since last rain.

column1: Lake level is down approximately 6 inches from normal in the spring.  Level is about at the same point when last fall's reading was taken.

column2: Lake level is at it's lowest since I started doing this.  Estimate of between 5-6 inches below normal depth.  Rain level of less than 1/2 inch in last month.  Water temp was recorded at 68.5 degrees F.
Lake level at 94.95 ft. or just .5 inches over the minimum lake level for spirit lake.
Lake is down 2+ inches below lowest level reading at exit dam.  .1 inch of rain late yesterday afternoon.
Received 1.75+ inches of rain in last week.  Lake is still 2+ inches below low level mark on exit dam.
We've had +2.25 inches of rain this past week.
Over 3.5 inches of rain in last 10 days.
lake is back to 1+ inches below the low level at outlet.  No rain in past 2 weeks.
